com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.arn

Class Arn

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.arn.Arn

  • public class Arn
extends Object
    The ARNs generated and recognized by this code are the ARNs described here: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-arns-and-namespaces.html The primary supported ARN format is: arn::::: Arn.getResourceAsString() returns everything after the account section of the ARN as a single string. However, the following ARN formats are supported where the values are present and well formatted through {Arn.getResource() ()}}: arn:::::/resource arn:::::/resource/qualifier arn:::::/resource:qualifier arn::::::resource arn::::::resource:qualifier Arn.getResource() ()} returns a ArnResource which has access to ArnResource.getResourceType(), ArnResource.getResource() and ArnResource.getQualifier(). To parse an ARN from a string use ARN.fromString(). To convert an ARN to it's string representation use ARN.toString(). For instance, for a string s, containing a well-formed ARN the following should always be true: ARN theArn = ARN.fromString(s); s.equals(theArn.toString());

      • fromString

        public static Arn fromString(String arn)
        Parses a given string into an Arn. The resource is accessible entirely as a string through Arn.getResourceAsString(). Where correctly formatted, a parsed resource containing resource type, resource and qualifier is available through Arn.getResource().
        Parameters:
        arn - - A string containing an ARN.
        Returns:
        Arn - A modeled ARN.
